result.name: Macau Harbour

reviews.text:
This is one of the worst Hong Kong style restaurants I have tried in HK and in the area within its international airport. I wonder if the Airport Authority has done any monitoring and survey to those business granted the operation license. This is very important to both local consumers and tourists' impression after their holidays here.

The following problems are noted: 
1) it's prices are 50%+ higher than that in the city
2) they are considerably  understaff
3) the attitude of staff is bad
4) food quality is poor. Hot foods are not hot enough, some are not even warm. The bread for breakfast was not heated, and I think the bread served for my breakfast had been selling for a few days which started to give out some smell
5) the food served was different from what was stated or photographed as in the menu, and they did not tell us when I placed my order; when I asked about it they said that it  had been changed without even a word of apology.
Ok place ok k food and you can hang out for a long time if not too many people
It is one of reasonable value with nice food at the Airport Food & Beverages,  Good

Very poor service, waiters very week.
Me and my wife place an order with starters (cod cake) and others main dishes. Only the main dishes arrived and after long time waiting the starters we asked the waiter about it and he said that he forgot to order, but the kitchen was close and they can't make the cod cake.
For me it's is a disrespect with the customer. At least do what was ordered. I'll never come back.
The menu is limited before 11am. Food is just normal. The noodle I ate not delicious, expensive with nothing inside. Very simple order, not much customers but I had to wait to long.
